    "Finally, we provide an outline of Mag-icTime (see Fig. 3) and discuss its implementation details.",
    "PreliminariesDiffusion models [49]- [51] typically consist of two processes: forward diffusion and reverse denoising.",
    "Given an input signal x t, the process of forward diffusion is defined:p θ (x t | x t-1) = N x t; 1 -β t-1 x t-1, β t I,(1)where t = 1,..., T are time steps, and β t ∈ (0, 1) is the noise schedule.",
    "When the total time steps T are sufficiently large, the resulting x t eventually approximates Gaussian noise ∈ N (0, I).",
    "The purpose of the denoising process is to learn how to reverse the forward diffusion:p θ (x t-1 | x t) = N (x t-1; µ θ (x t, t), Σ θ (x t, t)),(2)where Σ θ (x t, t) often does not need to be trained but is calculated based on the time step t as a fixed variance."
  ],
